Female genitalia (
Figure 5
): Only one female was available for dissection. Lamella postvaginalis distinctly rounded; lamella antevaginalis broad in the ventral plane, lined with moderately sclerotised longitudinal striae; ostial lobe heavily sclerotised, broad at the base and gradually narrowed into a sharp tip in lateral view, while the posterior margin is deeply concave with a pair of acute spurs in ventral view.

